Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: nose-descriptionfixer
Version: 0.0.3
Summary: A Nose plugin to fix the way tests are described when the verbose flag (-v) is used
Home-page: UNKNOWN
Author: Simon Weber
Author-email: simon@simonmweber.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: This is a simple Nose plugin that forces nosetests to print the full test name in verbose mode, rather than just the docstring.
        
        For example, given the test file ``example.py``:
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
            class MyTestCase(TestCase):
        
                def test_without_docstring(self):
                    pass
        
                def test_with_docstring(self):
                    """This is my docstring"""
                    pass
        
        This plugin changes the output of ``nosetests -v example.py`` from::
        
            This is my docstring ... ok
            test_without_docstring (vagrant.venmo_tests.example.MyTestCase) ... ok
        
        To::
        
            test_with_docstring (mymodule.MyTestCase) ... ok
            test_without_docstring (mymodule.MyTestCase) ... ok
        
        
        Install with ``pip install nose-description-fixer-plugin``.
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
